  "heading": "Community",
  "subheading": "At our core, we value respect, inclusivity, culture, and empathy. We've built a space where pros can chase Thirteen Orphans and newcomers can learn the game without feeling intimidated. For us, mahjong is more than just a game—it's a reason to get together. We're here to build a welcoming community where lifelong friendships are made and keep this tradition thriving for generations. We believe some of the strongest connections are built one tile at a time. — Jorge Yau, Founder of Lucky Cat Mahjong",
